summary:
The Security Council:

Recalling previous resolutions on Somalia, including resolution 2628 (2022) authorizing the African Union Transition Mission in Somalia (ATMIS),

Noting the African Union's request to extend Phase 1 of ATMIS for the drawdown of 2000 personnel until 30 June 2023,

Acting under Chapter VII of the UN Charter,

1. Reaffirms decisions in resolution 2628 (2022) with exceptions:
   (a) Extends authorisations until 30 June 2023, and affirms a strategic, gradual, and sector-by-sector approach to the drawdown of 2000 ATMIS personnel;
   (b) Notes the commitment to maintain the exit date of 31 December 2024 for ATMIS;
   (c) Requests a report by 30 April 2023 on progress made against agreed benchmarks;
   (d) Requests a further report by 30 April 2023, including a sector-by-sector assessment of security and ATMIS performance;

2. Recalls and reaffirms paragraphs 7, 8, 37, 38, and 52 of resolution 2628 (2022), and requests Somalia to provide an additional report by 30 April 2023, including an updated force generation plan;

3. Decides to convene a formal meeting on the transition in Somalia by 31 March 2023, with participation of Somalia, the AU, EU, and ATMIS troop contributing countries;

4. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
